This presidential memorandum delegates authority to determine whether it is important to the security interests of the United States to use up to $1.3 million in International Military Education and Training (IMET) funds to provide assistance to Thailand. The memorandum is issued under the authority vested in the President by the Constitution and the laws of the United States, and is subject to the requirements of section 614(a)(3) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961 (FAA). The memorandum also authorizes the publication of this memorandum in the Federal Register.